"A-Key Calculator v.1.0"

This program is a useful tool for cellular phone industry, TDMA and CDMA network
engineers and security managers, as well as everyone who is involved in developing
and testing the TDMA and CDMA handsets with the built-in authentication function
based on the CAVE algorithm as defined in IS-54 #Appendix A#, TSB50, TSB51, IS-95,
IS-136 and TIA-627 standards.

Now everyone can create a valid authentication key #A-Key#, 0 to 20 digits long, with
an accompanying 6 digit cheksum calculated for any given ESN number. The generated 
sequence of digits can be entered from the phone's keypad to reprogram the phone's 
A-Key for testing purposes or mobile phone activation. After entering those digits
the phone must display "VALID". This means that the new A-Key value is accepted.
Otherwise the phone will display "INVALID" which means that either the last 6 digits
of A-Key are not correct or there is a problem with the phone. With this program you 
can also validate an existing A-Key for any particular ESN number. The ESN can be 
entered in decimal or hexadecimal format, you can convert it from one format to 
another. A useful option is resolving the ESN prefix and determining the legitimate
phone's manufacturer. After you have entered enough digits of the ESN the legitimate
manufacturer name will be displayed automatically.
